description:
The investment seeks to track the investment results of the ICE BofAML US Corporate Index (the "underlying index").
 The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in securities of the underlying index. It may invest the remainder of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents, as well as in securities not included in the underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of investment-grade corporate bonds that are U.S. dollar-denominated.
